msgid "Monero Private Key Image"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:8
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid ""
"!!! note\n"
"    Author is nowhere close to being a cryptographer. Be sceptical on accuracy.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:10
#, markdown-text
msgid "Private key image serves to detect double spending attempts."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:13
#, markdown-text
msgid "In Monero funds are always sent to a one-time public key `P`.  Related one-time private key `x` is specific to unspent output."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:15
#, markdown-text
msgid "As output can be spent only once (in whole), the related private key can be used only once as well."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:18
#, markdown-text
msgid "Thus, specific private key image `I` being present on the blockchain means that related output was already spent, and subsequent attempts must not be allowed."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:22
#, markdown-text
msgid "This whole scheme is necessary because Monero uses Ring Signatures which make it impossible to know whom exactly signed the transaction.  This is why a simple Bitcoin-like double spending check wouldn't work here."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title ##
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:23
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "Definition"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:26
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "    I = x*Hp(P)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:28
#, markdown-text
msgid "Where:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:33
#, markdown-text
msgid "`I` - private key image (or \"key image\" for short)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:33
#, markdown-text
msgid "`x` - one-time private key used to unlock an unspent output"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:33
#, markdown-text
msgid "`P` - one-time public key of an unspent output"
msgstr ""

#. type: Bullet: '* '
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:33
#, markdown-text
msgid "`Hp()` - hash function accepting an EC point as an argument"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:35
#, markdown-text
msgid "The `P` comes from this:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:37
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "    P = xG\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:39
#, markdown-text
msgid "Where `G` is the [edwards25519](/cryptography/asymmetric/edwards25519) base point."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:41
#, markdown-text
msgid "Substitute `P` with `xG` and we get:"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:43
#, markdown-text, no-wrap
msgid "    I = x*Hp(xG)\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: ../docs/en/cryptography/asymmetric/key-image.md:45
#, markdown-text
msgid "The key image `I` is a one-way function of the private key `x`."
msgstr ""

